Write a code to get the input in the given format and print the output in the given format.

Input Description:
A single line contains a string.

Output Description:
Print the characters in a string separated by comma.

Sample Input :
guvi
Sample Output :
g,u,v,i
***************************************************************************************************
#include<stdio.h>
#include<string.h>
void main(){
    char ch[100];
    scanf("%s",&ch);
    int len=strlen(ch);
    for(int i=0;i<len;i++)
    {
        printf("%c",ch[i]);
        if(i<len-1)
        printf(",");
    }
}
